function clean_column(col)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), '-' => '_')
end
```

This function first strips leading and trailing whitespace from the column name using `strip`. Then it lowercases the entire string with `lowercase`. Finally, it replaces any hyphens (`-`) with underscores (`_`) using `replace`. The result is a lowercase column name with no spaces or hyphens, replaced with underscores.
